<br>
The idea of allowing other sneaky classes such as bards and rangers to be part of such a group did also cross my mind so if there are any bards and rangers out there who find such an idea appealing, please also contact me in game or leave a message below. Druids seem too dedicated to their cause to become thieves/rogues.<br>
<br>
Warriors too may be considered as &quot;Bashers&quot; for such a guild, acting as guards and &quot;protectors&quot; of people who need protection (you know...your house might just be broken into and all that, but for a small fee a month we'll keep your house safe *nod nod*).<br>
<br>
I would say that the above classes (rogues, bards, rangers and warriors) would set the entry restrictions. A rogue/thieve's guild would have very friendly relations with sympathetic  Enchanters, Mages, Shamans, and maybe Clerics and Wizards for various purposes (such as obtaining potions from them, or supplying materials for potions to them, etc) but will very likely have little to do with the 'up-themselves' classes who are dedicated to their profession, such as Shadow Knights, Paladins, Druids, Monks and maybe Wizards and Clerics.<br>
<br>
Gorgash, I agree that class-specific guilds that ally for raids would be a fantastic idea, but unfortunately, it would take such a large concerted effort to make such a thing happen that it seems almost unfeasible to do so.<br>
<br>
Thanks to all for their replies. Please make sure to contact me in game or via a message below if this appeals to you.<br>
<br>
Kraye <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sumataitherogue>SumataiTheRogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Forever LFG Rogue</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/11/03 1:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild of Rogues</span><hr size=1> When FV first started, there was talk of an &quot;unofficial, underground rogue guild.&quot;  It faded out.  Then, there was a FV channel for rogues, but ended up with only 3 regular members in the channel.  But....if you try to do something independant of guilds, I'd be more than happy to join with ya.<br>
